^B@2hondo717: Let me first discuss defensive planning. You have to try and visualize what is happening in all suits, not just trumps. It is important to play the correct cards on defense, so partner can work out what is going on. Unlike declarer, who can see all 26 cards of his assets, the defense can only see half their assets. Therefore, it is important that each partner card correctly, to give partner clues as to what they have. In this case, it was very important that aggie led the 5 of hearts, because just from that card, I could tell she didn't have the J and therefore, I was worried about kia getting pitches on hearts.|
PG| ***** 75 ***** |


NT|
^B@2hondo717: I also helped aggie out by playing the K of spades. when that wins, she knows I have the ace. If I had started with the ace of spades, she would not know who had the K. Again, carding was very important there. And finally, her 7 of clubs signal was important, to show me she had the K of clubs. Had she played a low club, I would have simply cashed the spade, so kia couldn't pitch it. As we see, defensive carding was extremely important on this hand. Now, finally, onto moe's double, |
