^B@2hondo717: Let me go over new minor forcing again. The idea behind new minor forcing is similar to Stayman, except it applies after someone has opened a suit and then rebid NT. As in this case, kia rebid 2N. You  want to find 4-4 and 5-3 major suit fits if possible. So mechanically, if there is an unbid minor (in this case diamonds), if responder bids that minor over the NT rebid, that is artificial, asking about the NT bidder's major suit  holding. The NT bidder's first obligation is to show a 4 card major if he has it. His second obligation is to show 3 card support for a major that responder has bid. In this case, since kia has both 3 card support and the other 4 card major, he should bid his 4 card major first.|
