^B@2hondo717: There is a subtle difference in new minor forcing depending on whether responder has bid hearts or spades. If responder's first bid was spades, as aggie did on this hand, and then bids new minor forcing, then responder must have 5 spades. Responder may or may not have 4 hearts, but has to  have 5 spades. The reason for this is, with 4-4, responder would have bid hearts first. Therefore, responder must at least be looking for a 5-3 spade fit. Responder might or might not also be looking for a 4-4  heart fit. in this case, aggie was looking for either. However, if responder's first bid was 1H, things are a little less clear. |
